  "text": "The spatiotemporal variability in malaria transmission was insufficiently taken into account in the 4 previous studies on the consequences of MIP, since no entomological data had been collected. In a recent intermediate analysis of data from the first 12 months of follow-up [CITATION_1] , we attempted to better apprehend children's spatiotemporal exposure to malaria using entomological data in the analysis, confirming its great importance.",
